.TH _PRINTF 3 "June 2025" "Holberton School" "Custom Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf - custom implementation of the standard printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"

.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function is a simplified version of the C standard library's printf.
It sends formatted output to the standard output (stdout) using only the
.B write
system call.

It handles the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.

.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed integer in decimal format.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal percent sign.

If
.I format
is NULL, or ends in an incomplete format specifier (e.g., a single '%'),
the function returns -1.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
Returns -1 on error.

.SH EXAMPLES
To print a simple string:

.EX
_printf("Hello, world!\n");
.EE

To print a character and a string:

.EX
_printf("First letter: %c, word: %s\n", 'A', "Awesome");
.EE

To print an integer and a percent sign:

.EX
_printf("Total: %d%%\n", 100);
.EE

To print a negative integer using %i:

.EX
_printf("Value: %i\n", -42);
.EE

.SH AUTHORS
Written by Alexander Zuleta G.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR write (2),
.BR va_start (3)
